After reading the other reviews, I used boneless chicken thighs. One slice of bacon and a tablespoon of butter. Im not sure why they suggest a non-stick pan, but I used my cast iron skillet. After watching Donnie Brasco on hulu, I dusted the chicken with flour, sea salt, and pepper. I couldnt find any parsley so I skipped it. Instead of shallots I used red onions and baby Portobello mushrooms. A few cloves of smashed garlic. Cabernet. After simmering for ten or so minutes, I added the flour for thickening. And then, it seemed crazy to put the whole thing in the oven, so I transferred the chicken to the skillet with the sauce and covered and simmered all of it together. What a great flavor. I served it with garlic roasted green beans and red potatoes. I would totally do this again, even if its not really coq au vin.

