Not a bad recipe, but a few things need to be altered to make it great. First, it should only be used with chicken thighs not breasts. Secondly as the reviewer from SF wrote, it really needs a good 30 minutes in the oven to incorporate all the flavors. Then finish on the stove, until the desired consistency in the sauce is derived. Mount with a half stick of butter, and you will have one awesome dish. With all of this, I still did this dish in about an hour. No need for the uncooked flour/ stock addition. Just spend a bit more time in the oven and the stove. Use a good rich wine like Syrah or Cab, and you will get raves...

Rating: 2
The reduction time in this recipe is way too short. After adding the flour mix, I added the chicken back in and simmered for 35 minutes, not 3-4 minutes. Only then does the sauce gain complexity. Otherwise it is thin and embarrassingly tasteless. In that 35 minutes the chicken also completes cooking and tenderizes. I recommend a good wine in the sauce; and I actually used less of it and more chicken broth. Next time I am also using chicken stock, not broth, if I make this again.

