Rating: 4
Absolutely phenomenal! Simple, hearty & wonderfully tasty. I did not have shallots or fresh parsley, so I used coarsely sliced onions & dried parsley - turned out exceptionally well :) Just to clarify a few things: Begin cooking the bacon in a deep, large skillet so you don't have to pour the drippings into another skillet for the broth. Just set the bacon aside after you cook it - on a paper towel, plate, cutting board...doesn't have to be a bowl. Cover pie dish of browned chicken with an oven-safe lid or sheet of foil, so it doesn't dry out. When boiling the wine/mushrooms/shallots/chicken broth mixture, it's okay if it looks somewhat thin after reducing for 10 minutes - the flour & any additional time spent simmering will even things out :)

